The aim of the course is to give an overview on anatomy and functioning of the nervous system, and on mechanisms, diagnostics, clinical features and management of the neurological diseasesObjectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the course for the students of stomatology is to learn the symptoms, the principles of the diagnostics and treatment of the most common organic diseases of nervous system. with special attention to the pathological syndromes and diseases of facial and cranial area (trigeminal neuralgia, atypical facial pain, headache).Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The course on neurology for the students of stomatology aims to give the knowledge on the symptoms, principles of the diagnostics and treatment options of the diseases of nervous system, with a special attention syndromes and diseases of facial and cranial area (trigeminal neuralgia, atypical facial pain, headache). After the course, the students will be able:  To understand functional anatomy and topical diagnosis of neurological diseases; To understand mechanisms of neurological diseases; To examine neurological patients;  To use diagnostic methods and investigations, and to make differential diagnosis of neurological diseases; To interpret clinical phenomenology of neurological diseases: disorders of brain, spinal cord, peripheral nerves and muscles;  To treat common neurological diseases. The assessment of knowledge is performed by an oral examination.
